\i\fs72 \cf5 \cb3 J
\i0\fs36 \cf4 \cb3 ames left behind a raft of classic blues songs that include \'93Shake Your Money Maker,\'94 \'93Talk to Me Baby,\'94 \'93It Hurts Me Too\'94 and \'93The Sky Is Crying.\'94 James\'92 distinctive style has influenced a legion of Chicago slide players, and his songs have been cut by the admiring likes of\'a0the Allman Brothers Band, Canned Heat,\'a0Fleetwood Mac\'a0and the Paul Butterfield Blues Band. \'93You can hear his signature riff at least once a night from every slide guitarist working,\'94 music historian Tony Glover has written, \'93but no one has ever quite matched that vocal intensity, which transformed the lonesome moan of the Delta into a Chicago scream.\'94\cb1 \
